properties.Name: Pipeline
properties.Description: A segment of a pipeline network fulfilling a specific function such as house line, service line, gathering pipeline, transportation pipeline or distribution pipeline.

Columns.Name: PipelineId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pipeline.

Columns.Name: FullRegulationPipelineIndicator
Columns.Description: A pipeline whose access arrangements are subject to full economic regulation

Columns.Name: PiggablePipelineIndicator
Columns.Description: A piggable pipeline is a pipeline that is designed to allow a standard inspection tool to negotiate it, which requires basically a more or less constant bore, sufficiently long radius bends and traps to launch and receive the pigs.

Columns.Name: IntrastatePipelineIndicator
Columns.Description: A natural gas pipeline company that is engaged in the transportation of natural gas within the state in which the gas is produced. Subject to regulatory oversight of the applicable state.

Columns.Name: InterstatePipelineIndicator
Columns.Description: A natural gas pipeline company in the US that is engaged in the transportation of natural gas across state boundaries and is, therefore, subject to FERC jurisdiction.

Columns.Name: PipelineTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pipeline Type.

Columns.Name: PipelinePurposeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pipeline Purpose.

Columns.Name: PipelineMaximumCapacityL
Columns.Description: The amount of oil or gas that can be passed through a pipeline over a given period of time.

Columns.Name: PipelineMaximumAllowableOperatingPressurePsig
Columns.Description: The maximum pressure at which a pipeline or segment of a pipeline may be operated.

Columns.Name: PipelineNetworkId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pipeline Network.

Columns.Name: MarketParticipantId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Market Participant.
